column5: Has the price for gas come down like it has in the U.S.?

Moose Jaw, Sask. - 54.4 cents per litre (cdn)It hase come down a lot. We were at a high of about 83 cents per litre. There's only one problem........the water is to hard to get the boat in!Merry Christmas & Good Fish'nMike M (Sask)

In Winnipeg it's been fluctuating from about 46 to about 54, with a few exceptions. I havn't figured it out for US gallons, but yes, it hasn't been this low since I bought my first car. Although I guess that was only three years ago.
